						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the Mādhavarāyasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Achyuta, 1531 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1452, Vikṛiti, Pushya ba. 14, Monday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1531 A.D., January 16, f.d.t. °46.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription is badly damaged and mentions Gōraṇṭla-sīma as the <hi rend="italic">nāyaṅkara</hi> conferred on the son (name lost) of Vākiṭi Mallappa-nāyuḍu.</p>						

